04/04/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Serbian and Montenegrin ruling parties reportedly have agreed on amending the federal law on co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. 
Serbia's ruling coalition Democratic Opposition of Serbia and Montenegro's ruling Democratic Party of Socialists agreed in principle on Thursday (3 April) to remove the article stipulating that the law applies only to individuals indicted for war crimes prior to adoption of the law in April 2002. 
(B92, BBC, Tanjug, FoNet - 04/04/03)
